{"css":".rd3-page {
    font-size: 14pt;
    font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;
}

.rd3-page .header {
    filter: hue-rotate(40deg);
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: 0 44%;
    height: 15em;
}

.rd3-page .header .content {
    width: 90%;
    margin: 0 auto;
    z-index: 1;
    max-width: 924px;
}

.rd3-page .header .content h1, .rd3-page .header .content h2 {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: #f6f6f6;
}

.rd3-page .header .content h1 {
    font-size: 13pt;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    font-weight: bold;
}

.rd3-page .header .content h2 {
    font-size: 32pt;
    font-weight: 200;
}

.rd3-page .header .bg-filter {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    background-color: hsla(0, 0%, 0%, 0.20);
}

.rd3-page .section {
    box-sizing: content-box;
}

.rd3-page .section .section-content {
    margin: 0 auto;
    width: 90%;
    max-width: 1024px;
    padding: 2em
}

.rd3-page .section .section-content h2 {
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
}

.rd3-page .section .section-content p {
    line-height: 1.5;
}

.bg-gray-050 {
    background-color: #f6f6f6;
}

.bg-gray-000 {
    background-color: #ffffff;
}","html":"<div class="rd3-page">
  <header
    class="header"
    style="background-image: url('/apps/molgenis-viz/img/home-header.jpg');"
  >
    <div class="content">
      <h1>MOLGENIS-coreRD3</h1>
      <h2>The minimal RD3 database</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-filter"></div>
  </header>

  <div class="section bg-gray-050">
    <div class="section-content">
      <section aria-labelledby="section-intro-title">
        <h2 id="section-intro-title">Overview</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>MOLGENIS-coreRD3</strong>
          The RD3 Core is a model and database that provides the structure for
          capturing and managing essential individual-centric data. It defines
          a minimal, standardized data model focused on core information about
          individuals, including identifiers, demographic characteristics, and
          basic clinical context.

          In addition, the datamodel is intended as a starting point for
          RD3-like projects and can be extended based on the specific needs of
          each project. For example, projects may choose to include additional
          domains such as samples, clinical observations, variants, or other
          specialized data. This core model provides a solid foundation upon
          which project-specific extensions can be built.

          It is designed so that all connections between existing tables are
          preserved and function consistently. Generic tables such as processes
          and materials are included to support extensibility and can be used to
          model additional concepts, including consent, files, experiments, or
          variant observations, allowing projects to expand the model in a
          structured and interoperable way.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section bg-gray-000">
    <div class="section-content">
      <section aria-labelledby="section-available-tables-title">
        <h2 id="section-available-tables-title">Data Tables</h2>

        <p>
          Data is stored in many tables. An overview of the primary tables is
          provided below or you can
          <a href="../tables/#/">view all tables</a>
          to find other metadata of interest. All reference tables and
          ontologies are stored in the
          <a href="../../../CatalogueOntologies/tables/#/">
            ontologies database
          </a>.
        </p>

        <table class="table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Table</th>
              <th scope="col">Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>
                <a href="../tables/#/Individuals">Individuals</a>
              </td>
              <td>
                An overview of the individuals (participants, patients, etc.)
                that are the focus of study. This includes demographics and
                clinical characteristics, as well as information of the data
                providers and references to related records within the database.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>
                <a href="../tables/#/Pedigree">Pedigrees</a>
              </td>
              <td>
                Overview of families (based on PED format). The definition of
                family members and the relationships between them are stored in
                <a href="../tables/#/PedigreeMembers">Pedigree Members</a>.
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>
                <a href="../tables/#/Processes">
                  Processes
                </a>
              </td>
              <td>
                A generic table used to register and describe processes or events within the system. It contains only the minimal core information required to identify and manage a process. Additional domain-specific details (e.g. clinical observations, experiments, or other process types) can be captured by extending this table with related fields or linked tables.

              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td>
                <a href="../tables/#/Materials">Experiments</a>
              </td>
              <td>
                A generic table used to register and describe materials or entities within the system. It contains only the minimal core information required to identify and manage a material. Additional domain-specific details (e.g. samples, files, consent records, or other material types) can be captured by extending this table with related fields or linked tables.
              </td>

            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>","javascript":"","dependencies":{"css":[],"javascript":[]}}
